CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1953, pg. 32, reads: "E. L. Smith, Builder, From Blueprint To New Community - New Homes Are News - Few Pittsburgh Negroes have ever had the privilege of living in a new home. Within recent years, E. L. Smith has built more new homes for Negroes than any other local building contractor. Operating principally on the East End - Penn Township sector, he has sparked the emergence of a new community in this area.  Here our photographer has taken pictures of phases of the Smith operation, as he converts raw land into a setting for graceful living. - Harris Photos."  "Ranch House - This deluxe ranch house is owned by Harold and Virginia Jones.  Built of brick and California cypress."
TitMainTitle: One story modern home with large picture window, carport or covered porch, and tree stump in foreground, 1349 Oberlin Street at intersection of Joplin Street, East End
